OL,6,FUnder the island's Firearms Law
OL,7,F(2000), Jersey residents may only
OL,8,Fpossess a gun if they have been
OL,9,Fgranted a firearms certificate by the
OL,10,FConstable of their Parish. They also
OL,11,Frequire these certificates to purchase
OL,12,Fammunition.
OL,14,FThis document costs #45 and is valid
OL,15,Ffor five years.
OL,17,FOn the application form for a firearms
OL,18,Fcertificate, islanders must provide:
